The cost of political participation for minorities and dissidents rose in more concrete ways. In New York, the police hate\uc0\u8209 crimes task force opened an investigation into multiple death threats against Mamdani, including voicemails threatening to blow up his car. These threats came amid a wave of Islamophobic attacks following his primary victory. His campaign increased his security detail. In Minnesota, the danger turned lethal. On June 27, state House Speaker Melissa Hortman, her husband Mark, and their dog were killed in their home by a man posing as a police officer. Another lawmaker and his wife were wounded in a related attack. The suspect, described as a self\u8209 styled \'93prepper,\'94 had a hit list of public officials. Hortman was known for her environmental advocacy and work for low\u8209 income Minnesotans. Her assassination, and the impersonation of law enforcement by her killer, struck at the heart of democratic life: the assumption that elected officials can serve without facing paramilitary violence at their door.\
