Universities and civil society organizations found themselves under similar pressure. DHS Secretary Kristi Noem threatened to revoke Harvard\'92s certification to host foreign students, accusing the university of fostering extremism; a federal judge blocked the move on free\uc0\u8209 speech grounds. The Justice Department opened an investigation into the University of California\'92s hiring practices, part of a broader campaign against diversity, equity, and inclusion programs. At the University of Virginia, President James Ryan resigned under pressure from the White House as part of a settlement of a DOJ probe into the school\'92s DEI policies, which the administration claimed improperly prioritized race in admissions and student life. These actions did not outlaw dissenting views outright. They used the threat of funding cuts and legal action to steer universities away from equity initiatives and toward a narrower, state\u8209 approved conception of academic life.\
